130 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL MOSCO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is about time for responsible journals to illustrate the fact that illegal 
aliens are just that: They are in this country illegally. The national 
consensus, as represented by current law, is that we, as a nation, do not want 
all of the world's poor people to move to the United States. 
</P>
<P>
It is indeed unfortunate that the world today is populated mainly by people 
living in poverty; it is equally unfortunate that the United States cannot 
eliminate world poverty by absorbing all of the world's poor into its 
population. Immigrant "rights" groups would serve future generations better by 
devoting their energies to advocating birth control in Third World countries 
rather than advocating absorbing excess population into this country. 
</P>
<P>
BRUCE DUNCAN ROSS, Santa Barbara 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
