<P>
FIRE CAUSES $250,000 DAMAGE TO CHURCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire early Saturday morning caused an estimated $250,000 worth of damage to a 
Mormon church in Sunland-Tujunga, a fire official said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire started at 3:57 a.m. at the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day 
Saints at 7955 W. Hillrose St. 
</P>
<P>
It took eight companies of firefighters 29 minutes to extinguish the blaze. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured and the cause of the fire is under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
The fire caused an estimated $200,000 worth of damage to the building and 
another $50,000 to its contents. 
</P>
