<P>
SHERIFF'S SPENDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's about time that the Shirley Grindles of the world stop their whining 
("Gadfly Buzzing Gates Over His Political Funds," April 22). These people are 
just political rabble-rousers with no understanding of what it takes to get 
things done in Orange County, and I'm tired of reading about them. 
</P>
<P>
Yes, Brad Gates spends lots of money on political meetings. But look what he's 
gotten out of them: support is growing for a new jail, his advisory council has 
donated almost a million dollars worth of new equipment and facilities to law 
enforcement, and George Bush himself came to Orange County to get our sheriff's 
advice on how to fight the drug war. And yes, Gates' wife is a hard-working 
businesswoman, and they do have rich friends. So what? His friends are the 
biggest employers in the county. We need the sheriff to enlist their support. 
</P>
