<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONFLICTS OF INTEREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is intriguing that the Sheridans plan to continue representing Irvine city 
employees in real estate transactions when it was not too long ago that they 
both admitted to me, when I was a realtor also with Remax, that the reason that 
they had worked in an extremely well known real estate firm in Newport Beach 
was because of the possibility of conflicts of interest. 
</P>
<P>
It is also very interesting to note that the Sheridans admit to being "commonly 
the listing agents for property sales in these transactions, which entitled 
them to a small percentage of the sale price." 
</P>
<P>
Most real estate companies share the brokerage fee 50-50, unless the listing 
agency agrees to take a lower amount than is provided to the cooperating 
agency. Let us not open the books and expose to the public all the tricks of 
the trade in transferring real estate, but let us examine in great detail the 
potential of the conflicts of interest. Herein lies the rub! 
</P>
<P>
ALAN BEEL 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
