<HEADLINE>
<P>
PIGMENT ENVY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dr. Frances L. Cress Welsing's theory about the origins of racism will no doubt 
trigger a deluge of mail from whites who feel their pants have been pulled down 
("Public Enemy and a Psychiatrist's Theory of Race," Pop Eye, April 29). I 
don't see how her pigment envy theory is any more ridiculous than Freud's idea 
that women have "penis envy." 
</P>
<P>
I am a white male who has lived in and loved black communities in Detroit, New 
York and Los Angeles. Whites who have been victims of racism by blacks ought to 
consider their own inner feelings. White communities are rife with idiots who 
make racist remarks unchallenged. 
</P>
<P>
I live in Hollywood because while there is still racism here, it is less severe 
than most parts of this country. Ironically, that is probably the result of the 
liberalism of the same Jews that Professor Griff of the Public Enemy rap group 
feels are responsible for "the majority of wickedness." 
</P>
<P>
FREDERICK CLEVELAND 
</P>
<P>
Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050690-0069 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 214741 </DOCID>
