<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARGAIN CORNER: ISLAND ATTRACTIONS IN PUERTO RICO BOOKLET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK ADLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A revamped "Island Attractions" booklet is available for travelers planning a 
trip to Puerto Rico. 
</P>
<P>
Many of the discount coupons in the booklet are for folkloric shows given as 
part of the year-round LeLoiLai festival, which celebrates the island's 
traditional music and dance forms. 
</P>
<P>
But the booklet also has coupons for lodging, sports, sightseeing tours, theme 
parks, car rentals, restaurants and shopping. 
</P>
<P>
The coupons, which may include free admissions to some museums and other 
attractions, cover such activities as a cruise around San Juan Bay, 
complimentary rum bottles during a guided tour of a rum distillery, golf, horse 
racing, snorkeling and scuba diving. 
</P>
<P>
You can buy the discount booklets when you arrive in Puerto Rico at $8 for 
adults, $6 for children 11 and under. The booklets are valued at about $120. 
Many of the special festival shows cost $5 or more for general admission. 
</P>
<P>
The booklets are complimentary if you book a minimum of four nights at 
participating hotels at regular room rates during the April 16 to Dec. 15 
off-season. 
</P>
<P>
Another perk is a 20% discount given for stays longer than four nights, Monday 
through Thursday, at a majority of Puerto Rico's country inns. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, contact the Puerto Rico Tourism Co., 3575 W. Cahuenga 
Blvd., Suite 248, Los Angeles 90068, (213) 874-5991. 
</P>
<P>
Farther north, 29 hotels and villas in the Nassau, Cable Beach and Paradise 
Island areas of the Bahamas are offering guests complimentary discount 
booklets, with more than 60 coupons covering: dining and entertainment; various 
sports, including golf; sightseeing attractions, including boat cruises, and 
shopping, which may entail free gifts as well as discounts. 
</P>
<P>
The coupons are good throughout 1990. Contact travel agents or the Nassau-Cable 
Beach-Paradise Island Promotion Board at toll-free (800) 327-9019. JACK ADLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
