<P>
CAR CRASHES ONTO BALLFIELD, KILLS 3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A speeding car veered through a baseball field in the Chicago suburb of 
Riverside, killing three children and injuring six other children and two 
adults before crashing into a building, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The car plowed through a fence into a bench, hitting people on the field before 
continuing across a busy street and ramming the entrance to a medical clinic in 
the adjoining suburb of Berwyn, police said. The driver, a man who appeared 
about 50 years old, was coherent after the accident and was taken to MacNeal 
Hospital in Berwyn, officials said. He may have suffered a heart attack, but 
there was no indication he had been drinking, officials said. 
</P>
