<P>
COLOMBIANS PLEAD GUILTY IN DRUG CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The reputed No. 3 man in Colombia's Cali drug cartel and an associate pleaded 
guilty to federal drug charges two weeks into their trial in Miami. 
</P>
<P>
Their lawyer had concluded the government had "an unbeatable case." The charges 
they pleaded guilty to carry a minimum term of 10 years and a maximum of life 
imprisonment. The government agreed to drop the most serious count, operating a 
continuing criminal enterprise, which carries a mandatory life prison sentence. 
</P>
