<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRUMPS PUB IN HOUSTON GETS WORD: DONALD DOESN'T LIKE USE OF HIS NAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Donald Trump may never set foot in the small southwest Houston bar but he still 
doesn't like its name. 
</P>
<P>
Ron Schaefer, owner of Trumps Pub, received a certified letter from a 
representative of the billionaire businessman ordering him to "cease and 
desist" false claims that "Donald Trump is endorsing your business activities." 
</P>
<P>
The letter from Joseph Silver threatened legal action if Schaefer did not come 
up with another name within 24 hours of receiving the letter. 
</P>
<P>
He said Trump owns the Donald Trump and Trump trademarks and that the Trump 
Organization has "people on retainer merely to do this type of work. We do this 
every day." 
</P>
</TEXT>
