<P>
Diann Roffe and Kristi Terzian, who carried the U.S. women's ski team after 
world champion Tamara McKinney broke her leg in a preseason crash last winter, 
were named to lead the 1990-91 team. 
</P>
<P>
McKinney, 27, who won the combined gold medal and took a bronze in the slalom 
at the 1989 world championships in Vail, Colo., was named to the A Team for the 
13th consecutive year although she is still rehabilitating and won't definitely 
return. 
</P>
<P>
