<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROFESSOR WILL RUN FOR SCHOLARSHIP FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Barcellona, a professor of music at Cal State Long Beach, will run in the 
Long Beach Marathon today to initiate a scholarship for his students. 
</P>
<P>
He is raising money through sponsor pledges for each mile completed. 
</P>
<P>
The University Woodwind Quintet, consisting of the music department's five top 
students, made the finals in the Monterey National Chamber Music Competition. 
Barcellona would like to start a scholarship to reward these students for their 
efforts and to continue to attract the finest musicians to Cal State Long 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Barcellona can be contacted at 985-4789 or through the university. 
</P>
</TEXT>
