<TEXT>
<P>
In "Lincoln S&amp;L Posts Loss of $1 Billion for Year," (March 28) the last 
line reads "the failure of the thrift . . . could cost the government more than 
$2 billion." 
</P>
<P>
This is wrong. It will not cost the "government" one cent because it has no 
