<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOT SPENDING MONEY CAN IMPROVE FAST FOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In "Diet for a New America," author John Robbins points out that fast-food 
hamburger chains are the principal offenders in the rape of the rain forests. A 
football field of atmosphere-nourishing trees are razed daily, primarily to 
provide pasture land for beef (despite clown-faced Ronald McDonald's 
reassurance that hamburgers grow in hamburger patches). 
</P>
<P>
Robbins, who points out that any ecological turnabout must begin on our own 
plates, suggests that every American who forgoes one quarter-pounder per week 
effectively saves an acre of rain forest per year. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN OETTINGER 
</P>
<P>
Hollywood 
</P>
