Map, Homes Owned by American Investments (per city); Table, Homes Owned by 
American Investments (per city); Photo, Los Angeles resident Jose Espinosa De 
Los Monteros, one of hundreds of Southland Latinos who were victimized, lost 
his $50,000. JAVIER MENDOZA / For The Times; Photo, "This case is very Alice in 
Wonderland," concludes state Department of Corporations attorney Dorene B. Wolf 
of complex investment scam. AKILI-CASUNDRIA RAMSESS / For The Times; Photo, 'I 
went there and I spoke to him before I gave him the money and he told me they 
were a company that had been in business 25 years. He said the money was going 
to be safe.' -- CATALINA TORRES, Investor of $40,000 with Jose Manuel de la 
Jara, above. Torres, who saw an advertisement for for de la Jara's company 
while watching a Spanish-language television station, has apparently lost all 
of her investment, investigators say. 
