<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO RE-WATCH: DONNA DEAREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOAN FANTAZIA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To most of Hilldale, Donna Stone is the perfect wife and mother. But those who 
watch her every move on Nickelodeon know that she can be a tyrant. 
</P>
<P>
Take the time she grounded the kids for disobeying her. Or when she made a 
thoughtless deliveryman go back and get the right item. Once she even got 
annoyed at daughter Mary for expecting her to make all her decisions. 
</P>
<P>
The only reason she isn't always a monster is that she's too busy keeping the 
house spotless, waiting on her husband and children, doing charity work and 
solving the community's problems. 
</P>
<P>
If you don't believe there is a dark side of Donna, just tune in to 
Nickelodeon's "The Donna Reed Show" marathon, which begins Sunday and runs 
through next Sunday-Mother's Day. This marathon isn't afraid to show Donna 
Dearest at her best and worst. The Donna-thon preempts regular Nick at Nite 
programming (from 8 p.m. to 6 a.m.). 
</P>
<P>
In some of her better moments this week, Donna will help out Buster Keaton 
(Tuesday at 2:30 a.m.), learn a lesson from trumpeter Harry James (Thursday at 
5:30 a.m.) and inspire singer Tony Martin (Saturday at 2:30 a.m.). 
</P>
</TEXT>
